  "text": "From the search engine's point of view, there is a cost associated with not detecting an event, and thus having an outdated copy of a resource. The most-used cost functions are freshness and age [7] . Two simple re-visiting policies were studied by Cho and Garcia-Molina [CITATION_1] :",
